body.description: See your papers at a glance and keep project pieces together. Smead’s Poly Expanding File Jackets are designed to help you keep projects organized and contents easy to see. These jackets in assorted colors have a full-length gusset to keep contents secured. Includes 10 letter size (11-3/4” W x 9-1/2” H) translucent file jackets in assorted colors, with 2 each of green, purple, yellow, red and dark blue. Pockets expand to 1” for greater storage capacity. Durable poly jackets are excellent for storing charts, photos and bulky documents that do not fit in traditional file folders. Straight-cut tabs are easy to spot in horizontal files. Use these jackets for receipts, class syllabus, important documents and travel details. Tear and water resistant, these jackets are easy to reuse. Poly is sturdy enough to keep papers neat in a messenger bag, backpack or briefcase. Make work flow easier when you can file and hand off your documents in a tidy sleeve. A simple change can boost your productivity and improve your organization.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I am organized!
reviews.reviewText: I love these folders!!!! I use a leather crossbody messenger bag that I decided to convert into a filing system---I am a university instructor and I carry all my tests and activities with me. I use post-it tabs to separate my papers and everything is organized beautifully. I love that I can just pull out the folder and put it back into its place inside of the bag without messing up my 'system.' The different colors help me to keep my classes separate as well by color coding them. If I were working on research, these would also be an ideal way to organize my notes and printed journals. They are also very resilient to everyday use. Before I bought these folders, I was using plastic pocket folders with brads. They could not withstand all of the papers that I needed to keep together and began to separate. These folders can handle a LOT of papers--they expand past an inch and have not began to separate at all. I would gladly buy these again and will as needed.
